by quality, peer-reviewed data.

00:45:59.880 --> 00:46:03.370
We covered this on the episode
on hearing and balance,

00:46:03.370 --> 00:46:05.610
but it turns out that white noise,

00:46:05.610 --> 00:46:08.143
which is essentially all
frequencies of sound,

00:46:09.080 --> 00:46:11.600
or all frequencies of
sound that we can perceive,

00:46:11.600 --> 00:46:12.860
mixed up kind of randomly,

00:46:12.860 --> 00:46:14.250
there's no structure to it,

00:46:14.250 --> 00:46:16.170
turned on at a low volume,

00:46:16.170 --> 00:46:18.510
not with headphones most of the time,

