01:20:37.980 --> 01:20:40.740
The first is that testosterone

01:20:40.740 --> 01:20:43.030
can exert its various functions only

01:20:43.030 --> 01:20:46.460
in its unbound form, free testosterone.

01:20:46.460 --> 01:20:49.500
We all make a particular binding protein

01:20:49.500 --> 01:20:51.890
called "sex hormone binding globulin"

01:20:51.890 --> 01:20:53.720
that essentially binds up testosterone,

01:20:53.720 --> 01:20:55.360
prevents it from being free.

01:20:55.360 --> 01:20:56.490
This sounds like a terrible thing,

01:20:56.490 --> 01:20:57.340
but actually it's a good thing

01:20:57.340 --> 01:20:59.102
because it allows
testosterone be transported

01:20:59.102 --> 01:21:01.340
to the various tissues,
including the brain,

01:21:01.340 --> 01:21:04.003
where it can exert its various functions.

01:21:05.770 --> 01:21:08.620
For those that have lower

01:21:08.620 --> 01:21:10.470
than desired levels of testosterone

01:21:10.470 --> 01:21:12.930
or too much sex hormone binding globulin,

01:21:12.930 --> 01:21:15.150
it turns out that 400 milligrams per day

01:21:15.150 --> 01:21:16.930
of something called "tongkat ali,"

01:21:16.930 --> 01:21:18.010
which is a form of ginseng,

01:21:18.010 --> 01:21:21.170
can actually help increase
levels of free testosterone.

01:21:21.170 --> 01:21:23.757
Many people experience a
positive subjective effect

01:21:23.757 --> 01:21:26.230
and some objective affects as well,

01:21:26.230 --> 01:21:28.200
meaning increases in free testosterone

01:21:28.200 --> 01:21:31.020
when they do blood analysis.

01:21:31.020 --> 01:21:32.160
There are some data on that,

01:21:32.160 --> 01:21:34.100
not a ton in the
peer-reviewed literatures,

01:21:34.100 --> 01:21:37.830
and again, always approach
these with a sense of caution

01:21:37.830 --> 01:21:39.920
and definitely talked to your doctor.

01:21:39.920 --> 01:21:41.130
If you want to learn more about that,

01:21:41.130 --> 01:21:42.470
you can go to examine.com.

01:21:42.470 --> 01:21:45.100
There's a lot of information
there listed about that.

01:21:45.100 --> 01:21:48.210
The other compound that's
relevant both to men and women,

01:21:48.210 --> 01:21:49.360
or I should say people that are trying

01:21:49.360 --> 01:21:52.663
to optimize testosterone
and/or estrogen, is Fadogia.

01:21:52.663 --> 01:21:56.090
Fadogia agrestis is actually an herb

01:21:56.090 --> 01:21:57.390
that increases the levels

01:21:57.390 --> 01:21:58.760
of what's called "luteinizing hormone."

01:21:58.760 --> 01:21:59.990
Luteinizing hormone is a hormone

01:21:59.990 --> 01:22:01.590
that's released from the hypothalamus

01:22:01.590 --> 01:22:06.270
within the brain that
travels to the gonads,

01:22:06.270 --> 01:22:08.030
either the ovaries or the testes,

01:22:08.030 --> 01:22:12.400
to stimulate the release of
estrogen or testosterone.

01:22:12.400 --> 01:22:14.970
And Fadogia agrestis has been shown,

01:22:14.970 --> 01:22:16.550
albeit in a limited number of studies,

01:22:16.550 --> 01:22:18.310
to increase levels of luteinizing hormone

01:22:18.310 --> 01:22:20.310
and thereby levels of
testosterone and estrogen

01:22:20.310 --> 01:22:23.030
in ways that some people find beneficial.

01:22:23.030 --> 01:22:24.200
So I just want to mention those two.

01:22:24.200 --> 01:22:25.950
And again, if you want
a lot more information

01:22:25.950 --> 01:22:27.760
about hormone optimization,

01:22:27.760 --> 01:22:30.263
please see the episodes
on hormone optimization.

01:22:31.280 --> 01:22:34.600
A key aspect to the mid-day meal,

01:22:34.600 --> 01:22:37.010
if you want that meal to benefit you,

01:22:37.010 --> 01:22:39.540
is to take a brief walk afterwards.

01:22:39.540 --> 01:22:42.410
It turns out that brief
walks of five to 30 minutes

01:22:42.410 --> 01:22:45.340
after ingesting food can
accelerate metabolism

01:22:45.340 --> 01:22:47.160
and actually can accelerate

01:22:47.160 --> 01:22:49.400
and improve nutrient utilization,

01:22:49.400 --> 01:22:51.110
which is essentially
the same as metabolism.

01:22:51.110 --> 01:22:53.890
But nonetheless, that's
something that I do

01:22:53.890 --> 01:22:55.840
after I finish my noon meal.

01:22:55.840 --> 01:22:59.710
I do force myself to
stand up and go outside

01:22:59.710 --> 01:23:00.670
and take a brief walk.

01:23:00.670 --> 01:23:02.640
That also gets me, again, into optic flow.

01:23:02.640 --> 01:23:03.860
It also has another benefit,

01:23:03.860 --> 01:23:06.300
which is that I am giving my brain

01:23:06.300 --> 01:23:09.360
and thereby my body more information

01:23:09.360 --> 01:23:10.590
about light and time of day,

01:23:10.590 --> 01:23:12.790
which is always better
than less information

01:23:12.790 --> 01:23:14.253
about light and time of day.

01:23:15.320 --> 01:23:17.960
Much of our circadian rhythm
and our health rhythms

01:23:17.960 --> 01:23:20.538
and all of our cognitive
rhythms, et cetera,

01:23:20.538 --> 01:23:25.120
are supported by our cells
knowing where they are in time,

01:23:25.120 --> 01:23:27.200
and light is the primary zeitgeber,

01:23:27.200 --> 01:23:29.230
that's German for "timekeeper,"

01:23:29.230 --> 01:23:34.020
is the primary way in which
the body learns information

01:23:34.020 --> 01:23:36.417
or about what function should be turned on

01:23:36.417 --> 01:23:38.260
and what functions should be turned off.

01:23:38.260 --> 01:23:39.560
So getting that morning light pulse,

01:23:39.560 --> 01:23:41.010
but then also leaving the house

01:23:41.010 --> 01:23:42.910
or apartment or workplace and getting out

01:23:42.910 --> 01:23:45.640
for a few minutes after lunch
is beneficial for metabolism,

01:23:45.640 --> 01:23:47.760
beneficial for nutrient utilization,

01:23:47.760 --> 01:23:51.510
and beneficial for all the
organs and tissues of the body

01:23:51.510 --> 01:23:54.270
because you're getting that
outside light exposure.

01:23:54.270 --> 01:23:55.540
Now I'd like to shift our attention

01:23:55.540 --> 01:23:57.950
towards science supported-protocols

01:23:57.950 --> 01:24:00.170
that increase the effectiveness

01:24:00.170 --> 01:24:02.500
and our performance in everything.

01:24:02.500 --> 01:24:04.350
And by everything I mean sleep,

01:24:04.350 --> 01:24:08.180
I mean physical performance,
I mean mental performance,

01:24:08.180 --> 01:24:10.920
I mean less anxiety, all the things.

01:24:10.920 --> 01:24:12.790
Truly all the things.

01:24:12.790 --> 01:24:17.020
And that is something called
"non-sleep deep rest."

01:24:17.020 --> 01:24:21.410
Non-sleep deep rest or NSDR
is an acronym that I coined

01:24:21.410 --> 01:24:25.800
as an umbrella term to
encompass many protocols

01:24:25.800 --> 01:24:29.130
that all have been shown,
in one form or another,

01:24:29.130 --> 01:24:32.350
to support better brain and body function.

01:24:32.350 --> 01:24:34.940
Now, these protocols have
names that you've heard before.

01:24:34.940 --> 01:24:38.490
Things like meditation,
things like yoga nidra,

01:24:38.490 --> 01:24:41.290
and things like hypnosis.

01:24:41.290 --> 01:24:44.200
All of these protocols and
these activities, however,

01:24:44.200 --> 01:24:45.410
share something in common,

01:24:45.410 --> 01:24:48.870
which is they involve a deliberate

01:24:48.870 --> 01:24:51.760
and directed shift in one's state,

01:24:51.760 --> 01:24:53.520
and the shift tends to be

01:24:53.520 --> 01:24:56.193
toward a state of deeper relaxation.

01:24:57.270 --> 01:24:58.570
We certainly don't have time now

01:24:58.570 --> 01:25:01.050
to dissect out the
literature on all of these.

01:25:01.050 --> 01:25:02.850
There is ample literature,

01:25:02.850 --> 01:25:05.510
I should say there is
robust and ample literature,

01:25:05.510 --> 01:25:06.620
supporting the fact that

01:25:06.620 --> 01:25:09.250
a regular meditation
practice is beneficial.

01:25:09.250 --> 01:25:10.990
But meditation itself has many forms:

01:25:10.990 --> 01:25:14.430
transcendental meditation,
loving kindness meditation,

01:25:14.430 --> 01:25:16.810
third eye meditation, walking meditation.

01:25:16.810 --> 01:25:18.420
Yoga nidra is a practice I've talked

01:25:18.420 --> 01:25:20.080
about many times before,

01:25:20.080 --> 01:25:21.620
which involves simply lying down.

01:25:21.620 --> 01:25:22.650
It doesn't involve any movement.

01:25:22.650 --> 01:25:24.230
No down dogs or up dogs or anything.

01:25:24.230 --> 01:25:26.110
It just involves lying on your back

01:25:26.110 --> 01:25:28.470
and doing some specific
long exhale breathing.

01:25:28.470 --> 01:25:30.080
There are a lot of yoga
nidra scripts out there

01:25:30.080 --> 01:25:31.820
that are quite good.

01:25:31.820 --> 01:25:36.010
But there's one NSDR type protocol

01:25:36.010 --> 01:25:39.500
that has been shown by the greatest number

01:25:39.500 --> 01:25:41.260
of scientific studies to promote

01:25:41.260 --> 01:25:43.660
not just states of deep relaxation,

01:25:43.660 --> 01:25:46.410
not just states of heightened focus,

01:25:46.410 --> 01:25:49.170
but also to accelerate plasticity

01:25:49.170 --> 01:25:52.140
and learning within the
brain, and that's hypnosis.

01:25:52.140 --> 01:25:53.930
And I've become increasingly excited

01:25:53.930 --> 01:25:57.240
and interested in hypnosis as a tool,

01:25:57.240 --> 01:25:59.740
and not just a tool of any kind,

01:25:59.740 --> 01:26:01.630
but a tool that really can be directed

01:26:01.630 --> 01:26:03.810
toward particular goals and outcomes.

01:26:03.810 --> 01:26:06.340
And I think that's really
what sets hypnosis apart

01:26:06.340 --> 01:26:08.940
as an NSDR, non-sleep deep rest, protocol

01:26:08.940 --> 01:26:12.130
from things like naps or
things like yoga nidra

01:26:12.130 --> 01:26:14.010
or things like meditation.

01:26:14.010 --> 01:26:16.430
And I certainly believe and understand

01:26:16.430 --> 01:26:19.660
that meditation naps and
yoga nidra can be directed

01:26:19.660 --> 01:26:21.780
toward less anxiety, et cetera,

01:26:21.780 --> 01:26:25.210
but hypnosis is unique in

01:26:25.210 --> 01:26:27.860
that it's very directed.

01:26:27.860 --> 01:26:30.950
The essence of hypnosis
is for the person, you,

01:26:30.950 --> 01:26:35.060
to guide your brain toward a
particular outcome or change.

