It's a really wonderful resource

01:27:45.600 --> 01:27:49.023
for which there is a lot of
peer-reviewed published data.

01:27:50.020 --> 01:27:51.640
One study I'd like to emphasize

01:27:51.640 --> 01:27:53.550
in particular is Jiang et al.

01:27:53.550 --> 01:27:55.400
J-I-A-N-G.

01:27:55.400 --> 01:27:57.550
That is a reference you can find

01:27:57.550 --> 01:28:00.640
on the reveri.com website
under Our Research.

01:28:00.640 --> 01:28:02.640
And the title of this
paper is "Brain Activity

01:28:02.640 --> 01:28:04.840
and Functional Connectivity
Associated with Hypnosis,"

01:28:04.840 --> 01:28:07.970
and it was published in the
journal Cerebral Cortex.

01:28:07.970 --> 01:28:12.320
What this paper essentially
shows is that specific areas

01:28:12.320 --> 01:28:14.880
of our brain that are involved
in executive function,

01:28:14.880 --> 01:28:16.860
which is associated with
our ability to focus,

01:28:16.860 --> 01:28:19.450
as well as what's called
the "default mode network,"

01:28:19.450 --> 01:28:21.340
which is sort of the way
that your brain idles,

01:28:21.340 --> 01:28:22.970
does your brain tend to idle

01:28:24.202 --> 01:28:26.820
at a level of high anxiety or calm,

01:28:26.820 --> 01:28:28.130
as well as activation of

01:28:28.130 --> 01:28:29.860
a brain area called the "insula."

01:28:29.860 --> 01:28:31.420
That's I-N-S-U-L-A.

01:28:31.420 --> 01:28:33.290
The insula is extremely interesting.

01:28:33.290 --> 01:28:35.920
Hypnosis has been shown
to activate the insula,

01:28:35.920 --> 01:28:38.410
which can enhance our
sense of interoception,

01:28:38.410 --> 01:28:40.370
our sense of internal state,

01:28:40.370 --> 01:28:42.290
which might sound like a annoying thing.

01:28:42.290 --> 01:28:44.520
You don't want to be
thinking about your heartbeat

01:28:44.520 --> 01:28:45.510
or your breathing.

01:28:45.510 --> 01:28:48.060
But what's really
interesting about hypnosis is

01:28:48.060 --> 01:28:49.523
that it increases areas of the brain

01:28:49.523 --> 01:28:52.810
that are responsible for
deep relaxation, focus,

01:28:52.810 --> 01:28:56.800
and self-awareness, this
interoception, simultaneously.

01:28:56.800 --> 01:29:00.220
And that's very unusual
compared to other states,

01:29:00.220 --> 01:29:02.240
any other states of any kind.

01:29:02.240 --> 01:29:05.530
So I've made it a practice,
a daily practice in fact,

01:29:05.530 --> 01:29:08.020
that after lunch and after this walk,

01:29:08.020 --> 01:29:11.000
I do a brief 10-minute hypnosis script

01:29:11.000 --> 01:29:15.000
because what I've found is
that in contrast to naps

01:29:15.000 --> 01:29:17.260
and in contrast to other forms of NSDR,

01:29:17.260 --> 01:29:20.520
it really allows me to enter
a state of deep relaxation,

01:29:20.520 --> 01:29:23.250
but also to then exit that state

01:29:23.250 --> 01:29:25.050
in a very focused and deliberate way

01:29:25.050 --> 01:29:28.090
that allows me to lean into
my afternoon in an alert way,

01:29:28.090 --> 01:29:30.990
in a way that I can
function and do mental work

01:29:30.990 --> 01:29:33.440
and interact with people, et cetera.

01:29:33.440 --> 01:29:35.930
So there's no brain fog,
there's no grogginess.

01:29:35.930 --> 01:29:37.630
And I want to emphasize that the hypnosis

01:29:37.630 --> 01:29:39.210
that I'm referring to here

01:29:39.210 --> 01:29:43.190
and that Reveri provides
is not stage hypnosis.

01:29:43.190 --> 01:29:45.295
This isn't you being programmed
to squawk like a chicken

01:29:45.295 --> 01:29:46.840
or do anything against your will.

01:29:46.840 --> 01:29:50.050
This is you teaching your brain
how to access these focused,

01:29:50.050 --> 01:29:52.530
relaxed, interoceptive states.

01:29:52.530 --> 01:29:56.090
This is also an extremely
valuable aspect to hypnosis

01:29:56.090 --> 01:29:58.790
because it can increase plasticity,

01:29:58.790 --> 01:30:01.170
the brain's ability to change
in response to experience.

01:30:01.170 --> 01:30:03.980
It's essentially opening
up pathways that allow you

01:30:03.980 --> 01:30:06.520
to change your brain in
the ways that you want.

01:30:06.520 --> 01:30:09.920
And it's very directed
toward particular outcomes

01:30:09.920 --> 01:30:12.180
So I am an, as you can probably tell,

